Author:
Vol / Page: 86
Edition:
Quote: SCELOGLAUX ALBIFACIES (LAUGHING OWL).- The history of this bird remained, for many years, a desideratum to naturalists ..[87] The uncontrollable outburst of laughter, i.e. the call peculiar to this species, is only heard when the birds are on the wing and generally on dark and drizzly nights or immediately [88] preceding rain.
